This paper deals with natural language processing and deep learning, which are both subfields of computer science. The paper specifically focuses on the problem of compositional generalization, which is a common challenge in natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a modification to standard approaches in neural machine translation, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of separate brain systems for syntactic and semantic processing, which suggests a connection to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses the SCAN dataset, which involves visual input, suggesting a possible connection to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision).
